-- Argentina Fines Claro for Service Cut, Ordered to Repay Clients
-- B y   S i l v i a   M a r t i n e z
-- 2012-06-06T21:38:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/argentina-fines-claro-for-service-cut-ordered-to-repay-clients.html
Argentina’s government ordered Claro
SA to return 9.2 million pesos ($2 million) to clients for a
mobile service outage on May 9. It fined the company an
additional 586,000 pesos.  The country’s Planning Ministry announced the measures
today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silvia Martinez in Buenos Aires at 
 smartinez19@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 